-- Copper Jumps to 27-Month High on Speculation About Fed Easing: LME Preview
-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 2010-10-11T07:14:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/copper-jumps-to-27-month-high-on-speculation-about-fed-easing-lme-preview.html
Copper surged to 27-month highs in
London and New York on speculation that the Federal Reserve will
increase measures to stimulate the U.S. economy, weakening the
dollar and boosting demand for commodities as alternative
investments. The metal jumped to a six-month high in Shanghai.  Market News:  Metals News:  To contact the reporter on this story:
